Haha awesome!! Always happy to help the DM team out!! 

Sure, adding a contact us form requires a little more trickery. They currently have a plugin installed called Contact7 which 'gets the job done', but we don't recommend it for a few reasons. 

We like to use the plugin GravityForms as it is more stable, flexible, mobile ready and also stores a copy of the message on the website (you can see submissions in the backend, export them to Excel etc). It's a paid plugin, but we can go ahead and set it up for you as we have a developer licence. 

All we would need would be:

  • The page(s) you want it to appear
  • The fields you want to collect (name, email, etc) 
  • Where you want a copy of the submission to be sent to e.g. info@domain.com.au
  • If you want the user to receive a copy as well 
  • Any messaging/copy above, below the form or to appear on form submission
It would take max 45mins and our hourly rate for customers not on a WP Perk plan is $125 inc GST. We will more than likely turn it around on the day as receiving the above. Let me know what you think, or if you have any questions?
